headline: Evaluating Cigna After Shares Dip 9% and Humana Merger Talks End in 2025
summary: Thinking about what to do with Cigna Group stock right now? You are not alone. Investors have been watching the company’s price movements closely, especially after a rollercoaster year that saw shares climb an impressive 76.3% over five years but fall 9.2% in the past twelve months. This kind of long-term bounce paired with recent softening leaves many asking if there is still value in the stock, or if risks have started to outweigh rewards. Dig a little deeper and the story gets even more...
